{"id": 227491316, "title": "Man killed in A38 three-car crash near M6 Spaghetti Junction as police arrest two people", "text": "Two people have been arrested on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving after a fatal crash on Birmingham's A38M this morning (June 2). The three-car crash happened on the Aston Expressway shortly after midnight. Despite paramedics' best efforts, a man was confirmed dead at the scene. Police said two people had left the scene before officers arrived but were later traced to an area away from the collision. Two men, aged 27 and 24, were arrested on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving and remain in police custody. Officers are scouring through CCTV and dash-cam footage. Read more: A38M live as police incident closes road in both directions near M6 Spaghetti Junction The A38M, leading to the M6, was shut for around 12 hours following the tragedy. The major route reopened at around 12.40pm today. Detective Sergeant Paul Hughes of West Midlands Police said: \u201cSadly we're dealing with a very serious collision and working with partner agencies to establish what caused this collision to happen. Our thoughts are with the family of the man that has sadly passed away. \u201cThe road has now been re-opened and I would like to thank everyone for their patience with the closures as we gathered evidence and made the road safe. I would ask anyone who witnessed the collision or has dash0cam and hasn\u2019t yet spoken with us to come forward with any information you have, no matter how small.\u201d Anyone with information should contact police by calling 101, quoting lof number 46 of June 2. Alternatively, information can be given anonymously by calling Crimstoppers on 0800 555 111.", "summary": "A man was confirmed dead at the scene after a crash on Birmingham's Aston Expressway in the early hours of this morning", "url": "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/midlands-news/man-killed-a38-three-car-29279947", "image": "https://i2-prod.birminghammail.co.uk/incoming/article29279320.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/1_WhatsApp-Image-2024-06-02-at-102738jpeg.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-02 12:26:28", "author": "Harry Leach,Stephanie Balloo", "authors": ["Harry Leach", "Stephanie Balloo"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.565}